-- Telefonica's Tuenti to Start Low-Cost Mobile-Phone Service, Expansion Says
-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 2010-11-19T06:30:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/telefonica-s-tuenti-to-start-low-cost-operator-expansion-says.html
Telefonica SA ’s Spanish social
networking site Tuenti will launch low cost mobile phone
services in coming weeks,  Expansion  reported.  Tuenti will use Telefonica’s network and will provide phone
calls charged at around 4 cents a minute for Tuenti mobile users
and 8 cents a minute to all other operators, the newspaper said,
without citing anyone.  Telefonica bought 86 percent of Tuenti in August for 75
million euros ($102.3 million), the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 